/* ========================================================================== */
/* Maintenance Notes */
/* ========================================================================== */
/*
 * TO CUSTOMIZE COLORS:
 * 1. All colors are defined in .chezmoidata/colors.yaml
 * 2. Change colors there, then run: chezmoi apply
 * 3. Relaunch wofi to see changes
 *
 * TO ADJUST SIZING:
 * - Window size: Edit width/height in config file (not CSS)
 * - Font size: Modify font-size in * selector
 * - Spacing: Adjust padding/margin values
 * - Icons: Change image_size in config file
 *
 * TO CHANGE SHAPES:
 * - Corner rounding: Modify border-radius values
 * - Border thickness: Adjust border width in window selector
 * - Entry shape: Modify border-radius in #entry selector
 *
 * SELECTOR HIERARCHY:
 * window
 *   ├── #input (search box)
 *   └── #outer-box
 *       └── #scroll
 *           └── #inner-box
 *               └── #entry (each result)
 *                   ├── #img (icon)
 *                   └── #text (application name)
 *
 * DEBUGGING STYLES:
 * 1. Use GTK Inspector: GTK_DEBUG=interactive wofi --show drun
 * 2. Inspect elements and test CSS changes live
 * 3. Check for syntax errors: wofi will fail silently with CSS errors
 *
 * TESTING CHANGES:
 * 1. Edit style.css.tmpl (this file)
 * 2. Run: chezmoi apply
 * 3. Launch wofi: wofi --show drun
 * 4. If no changes appear, check:
 *    - chezmoi apply ran without errors
 *    - CSS syntax is valid
 *    - File permissions are correct
 */
